<p id="p0140">The time of the classical behavior of the oscillator near its bottom (or, equivalently, far from the turning points of the nuclei) is much shorter than the period of the oscillations of the nuclei. This correlates with the fact in quantum-classical mechanics that the time of molecular “quantum” transition or, equivalently, the time of reorganization of the nuclear subsystem 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="M26" altimg="si22.svg">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mi>ℏ</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mo>/</mo>
     <mrow>
      <mi>E</mi>
     </mrow>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> (
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="M27" altimg="si8.svg">
   <mrow>
    <mi>E</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> is the energy of the reorganization of the nuclear subsystem as mentioned in Section 
 <xref rid="sec1" ref-type="sec">1</xref>), when, due to chaos in the transient state, the electron-nuclear system leads like the classical system (see above), is also much shorter than the nuclear oscillation period 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="M28" altimg="si23.svg">
   <mrow>
    <mfrac>
     <mrow>
      <mi>ℏ</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mi>E</mi>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak" linebreakstyle="after">&lt;</mo>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak" linebreakstyle="after">&lt;</mo>
    <mi>ℑ</mi>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>, where 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="M29" altimg="si24.svg">
   <mrow>
    <mi>E</mi>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak" linebreakstyle="after">=</mo>
    <mrow>
     <mo stretchy="true">(</mo>
     <mrow>
      <mn>1</mn>
      <mo linebreak="badbreak">÷</mo>
      <mn>0.1</mn>
     </mrow>
     <mo stretchy="true">)</mo>
    </mrow>
    <mtext> eV</mtext>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> and 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="M30" altimg="si25.svg">
   <mrow>
    <mi>ℑ</mi>
    <mo linebreak="goodbreak" linebreakstyle="after">≅</mo>
    <msup>
     <mrow>
      <mn>10</mn>
     </mrow>
     <mrow>
      <mo>−</mo>
      <mn>13</mn>
     </mrow>
    </msup>
    <mtext>s</mtext>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> (
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="M31" altimg="si26.svg">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mo stretchy="true">(</mo>
     <mrow>
      <msup>
       <mrow>
        <mn>10</mn>
       </mrow>
       <mrow>
        <mo>−</mo>
        <mn>15</mn>
       </mrow>
      </msup>
      <mo linebreak="badbreak">÷</mo>
